                            <comment id="12988856" author="gertv" created="Wed, 30 Jul 2014 04:24:16 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;On HP-UX, the correct way to undef a control character is &lt;tt&gt;stty dsusp ^-&lt;/tt&gt;. While setting up the console, JLine now issues a &lt;tt&gt;stty dsusp undef&lt;/tt&gt; causing the suspend control character to be tied to the letter &lt;tt&gt;u&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
Pull request &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jline/jline2/pull/160&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jline/jline2/pull/160&lt;/a&gt; fixes the JLine issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12992071" author="gertv" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2014 13:04:03 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by upgrading to JLine 2.12.redhat-002 (which includes the fix in pull request &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jline/jline2/pull/160&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jline/jline2/pull/160&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;on &lt;tt&gt;2.3.0.redhat-6-1-x-patch&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/karaf/commit/8a3962e8fb31ade15a04cf856e5f1fb51cfe2c1d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/karaf/commit/8a3962e8fb31ade15a04cf856e5f1fb51cfe2c1d&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;on &lt;tt&gt;2.4.0.redhat-6-2-x-patch&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/karaf/commit/c8f74e722a362c8a777b28575b9aa9ba341b7b4c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/karaf/commit/c8f74e722a362c8a777b28575b9aa9ba341b7b4c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Verified that the fix solves the HP-UX issues on {{ srt-hpux.lab.eng.bos.redhat.com}}&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
